<div id="col1">	
  	
<div id="s3hub-image"><img src="/images/S3Hub-Both.png"/></div>
	
<div>
	<h3>S3Hub</h3>	
	<p>View your S3 online storage, upload, download, set permissions, share with friends and more.

In order to use <strong>S3Hub</strong> with an S3 account, you'll need to <a href="https://aws-portal.amazon.com/gp/aws/developer/subscription/index.html/104-4018257-4816762?serviceID=8&servicePlanID=6&tag=ducktyper-20">sign up</a> first. If you don't want to sign up for an S3 account, you can still use <strong>S3Hub</strong> to view other users' public buckets.</p>

</div>
<div class="span-half">
  <h3>Features</h3>
  <ul>    
    <li>Queue files and directories for download or upload.</li>
    <li>Throttle your download and upload bandwidth.</li>
    <li>Simulate sub-directories. The folders you create are compatible with other S3 clients like S3Fox.</li>
    <li>Keep track of other S3 users you want to share files with or give permissions to.</li>    
    <li>Using the Share feature, you can automatically set permissions on newly uploaded files. You can also view what buckets other users have shared for you.</li>
    <li>Rename files.</li>
    <li>Near instant bucket to bucket copying.</li>
  </ul>
</div>
<div class="span-half">
  <h3>&nbsp;</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>HTTPS support.</li>
    <li>Growl notification support.</li>
    <li>Sparkle auto-update support.</li>
    <li>Set bulk permissions on buckets and files.</li>
    <li>Create torrent links and temporary URLs that expire.</li>
    <li>Preview for delete and permission changes.</li>
    <li>Manage bucket logging, creating buckets in other data centers.</li>
    <li>Custom headers, set on a file or append headers to a bunch of files.</li>
    <li>Drag + Drop support (to and from the Finder).</li>
    <li>More stuff coming soon, like syncing...</li>
  </ul>
</div>

